SIMPLE: enclave
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Enclave
<hw>En*clave"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F., fr. L.
<ets>in</ets> + <ets>clavus</ets> a nail.]</ety> <def>A tract of land or
a territory inclosed within another territory of which it is
independent. See <er>Exclave</er>.</def> <mark>[Recent]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Enclave</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Enclave
<hw>En*clave"</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>enclaver</ets>.]</ety> <def>To inclose within an alien
territory.</def> <mark>[Recent]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Enclavement</ent>⟦br⟧
